Posts.Content: I'm here today because I said in June I would report back. At that time, at age 73, a DRE came up with a nodule, PSA showed 4.7, biopsy negative. A 6 month redo PSA was the advice and in spite of much banter here I rolled the dice because I had faith in both my GP and the Urologist. Today was the 6 month PSA. 2.5. No further comments other than to thank those folks who were calm and positive. Tim.

Posts.Content: Originally Posted by MichiganMan16; Your age? PSA History? Dre History? How many biopsy's have you had? Originally Posted by Fairwind; The abnormal DRE justifies a second biopsy, this one specifically targeted at the nodule revealed by the DRE.. Sorry guys, I thought succinct would be the way to go and anything more would just take up space. Age 73 at the moment. DRE 2015; nothing felt. DRE 2017; nodule felt, first ever PSA ordered. PSA 4.7, first ever biopsy ordered. Bladder look see and ultrasound directed Biopsy reported negative for malignancy. Back to the simple question, nodule and PSA must indicate something, so why a negative biopsy? Not sure what more I can add.
